Delta of Zimbabwe Revenue Climbs 42% in First Quarter, IH Securities Says

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-07-28T13:25:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/delta-of-zimbabwe-revenue-climbs-42-in-first-quarter-ih-securities-says.html
Delta Corp. Ltd.,  Zimbabwe ’s biggest
company by market value, recorded a 42 percent increase in
revenue in the first quarter as beverage volumes climbed, IH
Securities said.  The brewer and soft-drinks maker’s revenue rose to $144
million in the three months through June from $101 million a
year earlier, the Harare-based brokerage said in an e-mailed
statement today. Beverage volumes increased 27 percent to 1.67
million hectoliters, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  